1
00:00:01,213 --> 00:00:02,202
ANGEL:
<i>Previously on</i> Angel:

2
00:00:02,373 --> 00:00:06,605
When I was a higher being, I could see
everything you ever did as Angelus.

3
00:00:06,813 --> 00:00:09,373
I love you, Angel,
but I can't be with you.

4
00:00:09,573 --> 00:00:11,086
This is where you were born.

5
00:00:16,933 --> 00:00:20,892
You never had a family or friends
or anything that's real.

6
00:00:21,093 --> 00:00:25,371
CORDELIA: And if this is the end, then
I want you to have something that is.

7
00:00:25,573 --> 00:00:28,610
Last night will always be special,
but it can't happen again.

8
00:00:28,813 --> 00:00:31,407
Take your new boyfriend
and get the hell out of here.

9
00:00:31,613 --> 00:00:32,682
- Get over it.
- What?

10
00:00:32,853 --> 00:00:35,003
There are bigger things at stake.

11
00:00:35,213 --> 00:00:37,044
Connor's scared you think
he's connected to the Beast.

12
00:00:37,253 --> 00:00:39,608
It does tend to show up
whenever he's around.

13
00:00:39,773 --> 00:00:40,842
ANGEL:
<i>We discovered the Beast's plan.</i>

14
00:00:41,013 --> 00:00:42,890
MANNY:
<i>To blot out the sun for all of eternity.</i>

15
00:00:43,453 --> 00:00:45,011
WESLEY:
<i>The sun, it's gone.</i>

16
00:00:45,173 --> 00:00:49,212
I had a vision of you, long ago, standing
in a field of bodies with the Beast.

17
00:00:50,013 --> 00:00:52,686
- This wasn't about Connor. It's about...
- Angelus.

18
00:00:52,853 --> 00:00:54,605
I don't know this Beast.

19
00:00:54,813 --> 00:00:57,566
But Angelus might. We need Angelus.

20
00:00:59,693 --> 00:01:00,808
NEWS ANCHOR:
<i>Officials from...</i>

21
00:01:00,973 --> 00:01:02,929
<i>... the National Weather Service</i>
<i>remain baffled...</i>

22
00:01:03,093 --> 00:01:05,891
<i>... as to the cause</i>
<i>of this strange phenomenon.</i>

23
00:01:06,053 --> 00:01:08,567
<i>All that's being reported</i>
<i>at this mid-afternoon hour...</i>

24
00:01:08,733 --> 00:01:12,282
<i>... is what meteorologists are calling,</i>
<i>quote, "a localized abnormality"...</i>

25
00:01:12,453 --> 00:01:16,332
<i>... confirming earlier reports</i>
<i>that outlying areas remain unaffected...</i>

26
00:01:16,533 --> 00:01:19,764
<i>... while the sun over Los Angeles has,</i>
<i>for all intents and purposes...</i>

27
00:01:19,933 --> 00:01:21,685
<i>... been blotted out from the sky.</i>

28
00:01:21,893 --> 00:01:25,124
<i>The mayor's office scheduled a news</i>
<i>conference for 6:00 this evening...</i>

29
00:01:25,293 --> 00:01:28,603
<i>... regarding this bizarre development</i>
<i>and what it may mean for the city.</i>

30
00:01:28,773 --> 00:01:30,570
GUNN:
I'll tell you what it means.

31
00:01:30,733 --> 00:01:33,691
As soon as vamps realize
this town's open for business 24/7...

32
00:01:33,893 --> 00:01:36,168
...there's gonna be a huge rise
in undead tourism.

33
00:01:36,333 --> 00:01:38,767
We just gotta find a way
to bring back the sun.

34
00:01:38,933 --> 00:01:42,562
Working on it.
Failing miserably, but working on it.

35
00:01:42,733 --> 00:01:46,567
I could really use some help deciphering
some of these symbols.

36
00:01:46,733 --> 00:01:50,043
Or all of them, really.

37
00:01:50,853 --> 00:01:53,447
I need Wesley.

38
00:01:54,333 --> 00:01:56,449
His expertise.

39
00:01:56,653 --> 00:01:58,803
Yeah, well, rogue warrior took off
without a word.

40
00:01:59,013 --> 00:02:02,244
After Electro-Gwen decided to skip town
when the going got tougher.

41
00:02:02,453 --> 00:02:04,330
Not big on the teamwork,
either of them.

42
00:02:04,533 --> 00:02:06,330
You're wasting your time.

43
00:02:06,493 --> 00:02:08,051
"The answer is among us."

44
00:02:08,213 --> 00:02:09,202
[INAUDIBLE]

45
00:02:10,733 --> 00:02:13,406
He knows. He's part of the plan.

46
00:02:13,613 --> 00:02:16,173
- He doesn't remember.
- So he says.

47
00:02:16,333 --> 00:02:18,722
You saw him yourself,
making a pact with the Beast.

48
00:02:18,933 --> 00:02:21,401
It wasn't Angel in my vision.
It was Angelus.

49
00:02:21,613 --> 00:02:27,449
- He is Angelus.
- Believe me, you've never met Angelus.

50
00:02:28,853 --> 00:02:32,129
Me neither. But I'm starting to think
maybe it's time we did.

51
00:02:32,333 --> 00:02:36,121
Maybe Wes is right. Big Beastie has got
to be stopped, and I'm out of ideas.

52
00:02:36,333 --> 00:02:39,052
If there's a chance Angelus has
inside info we could use...

53
00:02:39,253 --> 00:02:41,084
You think he's going to turn it over?

54
00:02:41,293 --> 00:02:43,045
I think it's worth a try.

55
00:02:43,253 --> 00:02:47,166
Not gonna happen. The Gypsies cursed
him with a soul so he'd feel remorse...

56
00:02:47,333 --> 00:02:50,405
...to make him suffer
for all the people he slaughtered.

57
00:02:50,613 --> 00:02:55,846
Removing that soul is the only way
to change Angel back into Angelus.

58
00:02:56,053 --> 00:02:58,283
A lot easier said than done.

59
00:02:58,453 --> 00:03:00,091
CORDELIA:
The Gypsy curse was specific.

60
00:03:00,253 --> 00:03:03,484
For Angel to lose his soul, he would have
to experience a moment...

61
00:03:03,653 --> 00:03:07,123
...of perfect, pure happiness.

62
00:03:09,093 --> 00:03:14,884
And right now, happiness of any kind
is in kind of short supply.

63
00:03:15,093 --> 00:03:17,926
- You sure?
- Sorry, bucko, I got nothing.

64
00:03:18,133 --> 00:03:21,569
Your choice of "The Night the Lights
Went Out in Georgia" threw me a wee.

65
00:03:21,733 --> 00:03:24,122
I'm personally not huge
with the Vicky Lawrence love.

66
00:03:24,333 --> 00:03:27,564
Doesn't make sense. I remember
everything Angelus did, I did.

67
00:03:27,733 --> 00:03:31,692
Every family butchered, every child
slaughtered, every throat ripped out.

68
00:03:31,853 --> 00:03:34,162
I remember every detail of all of it.

69
00:03:34,373 --> 00:03:37,012
So how come you don't have
a smidge of any recollection...

70
00:03:37,173 --> 00:03:40,370
...of a giant magma demon
with ram horns and goat legs?

71
00:03:40,573 --> 00:03:43,883
Hey, all's I can tell you, stud,
is if it's in there, it's buried deep.

72
00:03:44,053 --> 00:03:45,805
Deep inside Angelus.

73
00:03:46,013 --> 00:03:48,481
Then that's where it stays.
Even if I wanted it...

74
00:03:48,653 --> 00:03:51,167
...there's no way to bring Angelus back.

75
00:03:59,773 --> 00:04:01,445
[SPEAKING FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

76
00:04:15,453 --> 00:04:16,442
[CRASHING]

77
00:04:24,533 --> 00:04:28,924
Rumor has it you possess
certain skills I require.

78
00:04:30,453 --> 00:04:33,650
I need a soul extracted.

79
00:04:39,493 --> 00:04:41,882
Awakening

80
00:05:31,133 --> 00:05:33,249
- Did Lorne help you remember?
- No.

81
00:05:33,453 --> 00:05:35,409
- Anything at all?
- Nothing.

82
00:05:35,613 --> 00:05:37,843
- What've we got?
- A puzzle with missing pieces...

83
00:05:38,013 --> 00:05:39,446
...and some cryptic gibberish.

84
00:05:39,653 --> 00:05:41,484
Angel, whatever power this device had...

85
00:05:41,653 --> 00:05:44,565
...got swallowed up by the Beast.
It won't bring back the sun.

86
00:05:44,733 --> 00:05:47,042
- Without the orb, it's as useless as...
- Us.

87
00:05:47,213 --> 00:05:49,283
Face it, man, we're losing ground.

88
00:05:49,493 --> 00:05:53,042
Pretty much the only victory we can
claim is that we're not dead yet.

89
00:05:54,973 --> 00:06:00,331
Okay, look, I know things haven't been
going our way lately, but things change.

90
00:06:00,533 --> 00:06:03,570
We're not down for the count.
The Beast is not our only concern.

91
00:06:03,733 --> 00:06:07,248
Until we figure out how to end eternal
darkness, it's a devil's playground.

92
00:06:07,453 --> 00:06:09,728
Just the way you like it, huh?

93
00:06:12,053 --> 00:06:14,726
Something to say, Connor?

94
00:06:15,333 --> 00:06:17,164
You got a problem?

95
00:06:17,333 --> 00:06:18,846
- You.
- Hey, Connor.

96
00:06:19,013 --> 00:06:22,210
Acting like the big leader. Like we
don't already know what we know.

97
00:06:22,413 --> 00:06:24,005
And what do you know?

98
00:06:24,173 --> 00:06:25,970
Everybody thought it was me.

99
00:06:26,453 --> 00:06:28,171
CONNOR:
Maybe even I was starting to.

100
00:06:28,373 --> 00:06:30,967
It was you. You're the one
who's working with the Beast.

101
00:06:31,133 --> 00:06:33,169
- I'm not.
- Well, then you're a puppet.

102
00:06:33,333 --> 00:06:35,801
Either way, everything's going to hell
because of you.

103
00:06:36,013 --> 00:06:39,005
You're the reason that the sun is gone,
that I don't have a home.

104
00:06:39,173 --> 00:06:40,845
You're the reason that she...

105
00:06:43,933 --> 00:06:46,049
It's you.

106
00:06:46,333 --> 00:06:48,642
You're the reason my life sucks.

107
00:06:52,933 --> 00:06:55,128
Get over it.

108
00:06:55,973 --> 00:06:59,932
Not to be a buttinsky, but could we
get back to the pep talky thing?

109
00:07:00,493 --> 00:07:05,248
I'm not one to turn down a little pep,
but I'd much prefer we had a plan.

110
00:07:05,413 --> 00:07:07,244
WESLEY:
Here's one.

111
00:07:09,333 --> 00:07:10,971
Him.

112
00:07:11,173 --> 00:07:12,208
Who's he?

113
00:07:12,413 --> 00:07:15,530
Wo-Pang.
He can deliver Angelus to us.

114
00:07:17,053 --> 00:07:19,886
- Thought you said...
- Me too.

115
00:07:20,053 --> 00:07:23,682
Fred, would you mind brewing
some tea for our guest?

116
00:07:25,213 --> 00:07:27,329
Sure.

117
00:07:30,453 --> 00:07:33,684
Right this way, Mr. Pang.

118
00:07:33,853 --> 00:07:36,890
Any special tea you...?

119
00:07:37,053 --> 00:07:39,567
WO-PANG:
How about orange zinger?

120
00:07:39,733 --> 00:07:41,166
Oh, okay.

121
00:07:41,333 --> 00:07:42,971
ANGEL:
What do you mean, deliver Angelus?

122
00:07:43,133 --> 00:07:44,122
Wo-Pang's a shaman.

123
00:07:44,293 --> 00:07:45,726
Order of the Kun-Sun-Dai.

124
00:07:45,893 --> 00:07:48,885
Dark mystics? You brought a dark mystic
here without talking to me?

125
00:07:49,053 --> 00:07:51,089
He claims he has the power
to extract souls.

126
00:07:51,253 --> 00:07:53,892
- Claims?
- More importantly, he can restore them.

127
00:07:54,053 --> 00:07:56,362
Once we learn what Angelus knows
about the Beast...

128
00:07:56,573 --> 00:07:58,564
We're not bringing Angelus.

129
00:07:58,733 --> 00:08:00,769
- You don't have a choice.
- I do. That was it.

130
00:08:00,933 --> 00:08:04,562
- Wanna hear it again? Not bringing.
- Don't make it harder than it has to be.

131
00:08:04,773 --> 00:08:08,402
There's no plan B, and we're running out
of time. People are in serious danger.

132
00:08:08,573 --> 00:08:11,645
Then unleashing Angelus is
the last thing that we should do.

133
00:08:11,853 --> 00:08:13,969
If he's here, I'm not.

134
00:08:14,133 --> 00:08:17,409
I won't be able to protect anyone
from the Beast, or from me.

135
00:08:18,133 --> 00:08:20,044
It's only temporary.

136
00:08:20,253 --> 00:08:23,962
We'll take all the necessary precautions
in the interim, contain you.

137
00:08:25,773 --> 00:08:27,172
I'm not blind to the risks.

138
00:08:27,333 --> 00:08:29,893
- I know what Angelus...
- You have no idea...

139
00:08:30,053 --> 00:08:32,044
...what Angelus is, Wesley.

140
00:08:32,253 --> 00:08:34,767
All you know is what you've read
in books.

141
00:08:34,973 --> 00:08:37,089
You've never had the pleasure
of his company.

142
00:08:37,253 --> 00:08:39,244
And you're not going to.

143
00:08:39,453 --> 00:08:41,921
Get rid of the shaman.

144
00:08:49,853 --> 00:08:50,842
[DOOR CLOSES]

145
00:09:05,453 --> 00:09:08,092
They're all going to die.

146
00:09:08,293 --> 00:09:10,648
The flowers...

147
00:09:11,933 --> 00:09:15,403
...plants, trees...

148
00:09:15,613 --> 00:09:17,649
...without sun.

149
00:09:21,453 --> 00:09:24,047
Just realizing.

150
00:09:30,253 --> 00:09:33,848
I just came to say...

151
00:09:34,053 --> 00:09:35,725
...that I'm on your side.

152
00:09:36,453 --> 00:09:40,162
Angelus is the jumbo family-size bad
of bad ideas.

153
00:09:40,373 --> 00:09:43,365
He'd be a danger to all of us.
You made the right call.

154
00:09:43,533 --> 00:09:47,446
Wesley, the others, they don't get it.

155
00:09:48,133 --> 00:09:50,328
But you do.

156
00:09:50,733 --> 00:09:54,567
Well, if I didn't when Angelus
was loose and killing in Sunnydale...

157
00:09:54,733 --> 00:09:58,282
...then reliving his past horrors in virtual,
wide-screen Sensurround...

158
00:09:58,453 --> 00:10:01,889
...during my tenure in floaty-ville
pretty much makes me an expert.

159
00:10:02,093 --> 00:10:03,924
Right.

160
00:10:08,533 --> 00:10:11,570
Do you...?
Do you think Connor's right?

161
00:10:11,733 --> 00:10:15,089
That I'm being used by the Beast
without even knowing?

162
00:10:15,253 --> 00:10:16,971
No.

163
00:10:17,533 --> 00:10:19,763
Are you just saying that?

164
00:10:19,933 --> 00:10:23,243
Yes. I don't know, Angel. It's possible.

165
00:10:23,413 --> 00:10:26,485
Well, if I am, then I'm already a danger
to you. All of you.

166
00:10:26,653 --> 00:10:31,283
Well, not like Angelus would be.
I mean, he's...

167
00:10:31,453 --> 00:10:33,205
He's smart.

168
00:10:33,933 --> 00:10:36,128
Excuse me?

169
00:10:36,453 --> 00:10:39,365
Well, you know what I mean.

170
00:10:39,573 --> 00:10:42,645
- You're saying Angelus is smarter.
- No. I mean...

171
00:10:43,773 --> 00:10:45,729
...you're smart.

172
00:10:45,933 --> 00:10:47,252
He's just...

173
00:10:47,853 --> 00:10:50,492
- Ingenious.
- But in that twisted, sadistic...

174
00:10:50,653 --> 00:10:53,087
...ruthless kind of way.
- Like the Beast.

175
00:10:53,293 --> 00:10:57,332
Yes, exactly. They think alike.
Always a step or two ahead of us.

176
00:10:57,653 --> 00:11:01,566
I mean, what is it about evil
that jacks up the IQ points?

177
00:11:01,733 --> 00:11:03,530
It's like whenever...

178
00:11:04,853 --> 00:11:06,650
What?

179
00:11:08,973 --> 00:11:11,168
Angel?

180
00:11:12,253 --> 00:11:13,572
We're gonna need a cage.

181
00:11:13,733 --> 00:11:15,485
LORNE: A cage?
- A strong one, 10 by 12...

182
00:11:15,653 --> 00:11:19,487
...steel-reinforced, 2-inch bars,
maybe 3.

183
00:11:19,653 --> 00:11:22,042
ANGEL:
I'll make some calls.

184
00:11:24,333 --> 00:11:26,608
He thinks something like that
will hold the Beast?

185
00:11:26,773 --> 00:11:28,889
It's not for the Beast.

186
00:11:29,053 --> 00:11:31,248
It's for him.

187
00:11:44,653 --> 00:11:46,723
That's it then.

188
00:11:52,933 --> 00:11:54,844
[CLANGING]

189
00:11:55,053 --> 00:11:57,442
- You got it?
- Yeah.

190
00:12:11,053 --> 00:12:12,964
The cage is solid, man.

191
00:12:13,133 --> 00:12:16,921
All right, tell the shaman we're ready.

192
00:12:17,453 --> 00:12:20,968
Hey, listen, Angel-cakes,
if it's all the same with you...

193
00:12:21,133 --> 00:12:23,283
...I think I might sit this one out
upstairs.

194
00:12:23,453 --> 00:12:27,287
You know how dark magic unleashing
unspeakable evil gives me the heebies.

195
00:12:27,453 --> 00:12:30,684
It's okay. Tell Cordy and Fred they
don't need to be down here either.

196
00:12:30,853 --> 00:12:34,084
Gotcha, chief. Break a leg.

197
00:12:34,253 --> 00:12:35,971
ANGEL:
Connor.

198
00:12:36,133 --> 00:12:37,327
What?

199
00:12:37,853 --> 00:12:41,687
Look, I know you like to think
that I'm the enemy.

200
00:12:42,533 --> 00:12:47,243
But if this works, I will be.

201
00:12:47,933 --> 00:12:51,528
ANGEL: I'm gonna become the one thing
you were raised to believe I was.

202
00:12:51,733 --> 00:12:55,248
The thing I never, never wanted you
to see.

203
00:12:55,853 --> 00:12:58,925
Yeah. I think I can handle it.

204
00:12:59,093 --> 00:13:00,082
Uh-huh.

205
00:13:00,253 --> 00:13:03,563
Well, just keep in mind
that whatever Angelus says...

206
00:13:03,733 --> 00:13:07,089
...whatever he does, remember...

207
00:13:07,253 --> 00:13:09,289
...he's not your father.

208
00:13:09,453 --> 00:13:10,886
I am.

209
00:13:11,653 --> 00:13:14,451
ANGEL:
No matter what happens...

210
00:13:17,053 --> 00:13:19,248
...or happened...

211
00:13:21,333 --> 00:13:22,925
...I love you.

212
00:13:31,133 --> 00:13:32,612
Look, one more thing.

213
00:13:32,773 --> 00:13:36,561
Since I'm gonna be out of commission
for a while, I want you to, you know...

214
00:13:36,733 --> 00:13:40,009
...take care of everybody,
keep them safe.

215
00:13:40,213 --> 00:13:43,444
That means if anything should go wrong
with Angelus...

216
00:13:44,533 --> 00:13:47,047
...you're gonna have to kill me.
- Okay.

217
00:13:47,253 --> 00:13:49,687
If anything goes wrong.

218
00:13:49,853 --> 00:13:51,684
Right. I got it.

219
00:14:08,253 --> 00:14:09,925
- What is that?
WO-PANG: It is the Muo-ping.

220
00:14:10,133 --> 00:14:12,522
The receptacle
that will house his soul.

221
00:14:12,733 --> 00:14:14,212
Cordy, I don't want you here.

222
00:14:14,373 --> 00:14:17,092
Yeah? Tough.

223
00:14:30,333 --> 00:14:34,121
WO-PANG: It would be wise for your
safety to add a second lock to the door.

224
00:14:34,333 --> 00:14:35,971
Do as he says.

225
00:14:47,053 --> 00:14:49,123
Angel...

226
00:14:49,693 --> 00:14:51,649
...you don't have to do this.

227
00:14:52,133 --> 00:14:53,885
Now she tells me.

228
00:14:54,053 --> 00:14:57,807
WO-PANG: Close your eyes and don't
speak.

229
00:15:03,773 --> 00:15:05,684
[SPEAKING FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

230
00:15:24,453 --> 00:15:27,729
WO-PANG: Time to say goodbye.

231
00:15:34,573 --> 00:15:36,086
Gunn!

232
00:15:36,293 --> 00:15:38,761
CORDELIA: Hurry!
WO-PANG: Fool! Why would I help you?

233
00:15:38,933 --> 00:15:40,366
I serve the Awakened One.

234
00:15:40,573 --> 00:15:42,131
Little help here, please.

235
00:16:02,053 --> 00:16:06,649
So this was all a setup, this whole
soul colonic thing. For what?

236
00:16:07,493 --> 00:16:09,563
That's what I'd like to know.

237
00:16:11,133 --> 00:16:13,886
ANGEL: Why does the Beast
suddenly want me dead?

238
00:16:14,053 --> 00:16:17,841
Did Angelus welsh on our pact?
Is that it?

239
00:16:18,453 --> 00:16:23,481
Okay, then maybe you can shed a little
light as to what the Beast's plan is.

240
00:16:25,533 --> 00:16:29,321
Or maybe I should just start
taking you apart now, piece...

241
00:16:34,893 --> 00:16:36,724
...by piece.

242
00:16:37,133 --> 00:16:40,523
Well, so much for that font
of information.

243
00:16:40,733 --> 00:16:43,930
Gunn, see if he has anything on him.

244
00:16:54,653 --> 00:16:57,087
He's got something on him, all right.

245
00:17:01,213 --> 00:17:04,569
LORNE: Is there any part of this guy
that doesn't have writing all over it?

246
00:17:04,773 --> 00:17:06,286
Scratch that. I don't wanna know.

247
00:17:06,453 --> 00:17:09,729
- Can you translate it?
- Most of it. Definitely scripture.

248
00:17:10,653 --> 00:17:15,124
A recorded history of the Kun-Sun-Dai.
They're acolytes of the Beast, all right.

249
00:17:15,293 --> 00:17:16,612
GUNN:
That's why we couldn't find...

250
00:17:16,773 --> 00:17:18,729
...anything written about Beastie Boy
in the books.

251
00:17:18,933 --> 00:17:20,366
They have it on their asses.

252
00:17:20,533 --> 00:17:22,251
WESLEY: Hang on.
- What is it?

253
00:17:22,853 --> 00:17:24,923
WESLEY:
There's a passage here.

254
00:17:25,133 --> 00:17:27,044
- Difficult to... Fred, could you...?
- Oh.

255
00:17:27,413 --> 00:17:28,402
Uh-huh.

256
00:17:28,573 --> 00:17:33,966
It's detailing the acolytes' victory
over the Bosh M'ad sometime in...

257
00:17:34,133 --> 00:17:35,452
I think in the third century.

258
00:17:35,613 --> 00:17:38,685
What's Bosh... Whatever you said?

259
00:17:38,853 --> 00:17:40,809
The Opposers of the Awakening.

260
00:17:41,013 --> 00:17:44,289
The Bosh M'ad forged something
to destroy the Beast.

261
00:17:44,493 --> 00:17:47,769
WESLEY: The tooth of light.
- They made a tooth?

262
00:17:47,933 --> 00:17:50,493
To the best of my interpretation,
a weapon of some kind.

263
00:17:50,693 --> 00:17:52,411
How'd it work out for them?

264
00:17:53,733 --> 00:17:56,691
It was never used.
The Awakening was centuries away.

265
00:17:56,893 --> 00:17:59,566
In the meantime, every last one
of the Bosh M'ad...

266
00:17:59,733 --> 00:18:02,088
...was wiped out
by the Beast's acolytes.

267
00:18:02,253 --> 00:18:05,768
So this tooth thing must have had
them worried.

268
00:18:05,933 --> 00:18:07,286
What happened to it?

269
00:18:07,493 --> 00:18:08,687
Never found.

270
00:18:08,853 --> 00:18:10,730
The Opposers kept it hidden.

271
00:18:10,933 --> 00:18:13,049
So now we have to find a tooth
in a haystack.

272
00:18:13,333 --> 00:18:15,210
We don't even know
what the weapon is.

273
00:18:17,133 --> 00:18:19,283
It's a sword.

274
00:18:19,493 --> 00:18:21,370
The sword of Bosh M'ad.

275
00:18:21,733 --> 00:18:23,086
CORDELIA:
I can see it.

276
00:18:23,453 --> 00:18:25,648
Pretty.

277
00:18:27,933 --> 00:18:29,207
I know where it is.

278
00:18:29,413 --> 00:18:31,768
- Where?
- It's here, under the city.

279
00:18:31,933 --> 00:18:33,446
Well, that's a break.

280
00:18:33,613 --> 00:18:35,331
Did you hear that? There's a sword.

281
00:18:35,533 --> 00:18:36,966
ANGEL:
A sword to kill the Beast.

282
00:18:37,173 --> 00:18:41,086
You wanted to turn me into Angelus by
having an evil shaman cut off my head.

283
00:18:41,253 --> 00:18:43,642
Not that that wasn't a swell plan too.

284
00:18:45,933 --> 00:18:47,730
Sorry.

285
00:18:52,853 --> 00:18:55,731
Was that an apology?

286
00:18:58,933 --> 00:19:00,571
I was careless.

287
00:19:00,733 --> 00:19:04,123
Made a mistake that almost cost you
your life.

288
00:19:05,733 --> 00:19:08,566
Would've made pulling you out
of the ocean a waste of my time.

289
00:19:08,853 --> 00:19:11,925
Yeah, that would've been a drag.

290
00:19:13,053 --> 00:19:16,762
It's just the first time I ever heard
you apologize...

291
00:19:16,933 --> 00:19:19,242
...about anything.

292
00:19:22,773 --> 00:19:26,129
So we gonna go get the sword,
or what?

293
00:19:33,053 --> 00:19:34,771
ANGEL: I don't get this.
WESLEY: What?

294
00:19:34,933 --> 00:19:38,687
How is it a sword from the third century
is conveniently located...

295
00:19:38,853 --> 00:19:40,764
...here in Los Angeles?

296
00:19:40,933 --> 00:19:43,163
I don't think it is.

297
00:19:43,333 --> 00:19:47,565
I mean, I get the impression
that somehow it's accessible...

298
00:19:47,733 --> 00:19:50,884
...from, like, 100 points
all over the world.

299
00:19:51,053 --> 00:19:52,566
How's that work?

300
00:19:52,733 --> 00:19:56,203
I don't know. I just get the visions,
not the Cliff Notes.

301
00:19:57,053 --> 00:20:00,250
Over there. What's that?

302
00:20:05,933 --> 00:20:08,049
The way down.

303
00:20:09,333 --> 00:20:13,087
That's a steep grade down there.
Gonna have to take it a little slow.

304
00:20:13,253 --> 00:20:15,369
Watch our steps and stay...

305
00:20:15,533 --> 00:20:17,444
...together.

306
00:20:23,853 --> 00:20:24,842
Oh.

307
00:20:25,253 --> 00:20:27,608
- Connor.
- Found something.

308
00:20:31,533 --> 00:20:35,128
Easy, easy.

309
00:20:35,973 --> 00:20:41,047
What are those? Holiday decorations left
over from some S & M bondage party?

310
00:20:42,053 --> 00:20:43,645
[LOUD CLANGING]

311
00:20:47,733 --> 00:20:50,167
Wood. Why did it have to be wood?

312
00:20:50,373 --> 00:20:53,888
We have to pass through the corridor
without ringing any of the bells.

313
00:20:55,733 --> 00:20:58,486
I knew you two would get me
in trouble some day.

314
00:21:33,893 --> 00:21:35,451
Cordelia, freeze!

315
00:21:36,133 --> 00:21:37,691
Your sleeve.

316
00:22:24,133 --> 00:22:26,601
- Oh, no.
- It's a dead end.

317
00:22:26,773 --> 00:22:29,082
Who booby-traps a dead end?
That's just not right.

318
00:22:29,293 --> 00:22:31,648
There's something here.

319
00:22:33,013 --> 00:22:36,130
- Assyrian?
- Hebrew.

320
00:22:36,653 --> 00:22:38,086
Rashi script.

321
00:22:38,253 --> 00:22:39,481
Can you read it?

322
00:22:39,653 --> 00:22:42,645
Well, they're just random letters,
one on each stone.

323
00:22:42,853 --> 00:22:45,128
Unless...

324
00:22:49,933 --> 00:22:51,764
This is it! You did...

325
00:22:53,173 --> 00:22:55,289
- You didn't.
- There's a pattern.

326
00:22:55,453 --> 00:22:58,889
Hebrew letters have numerical values.
<i>Aleph</i> is one.

327
00:22:59,053 --> 00:23:03,092
The letter with the next highest
numerical value would be <i>he</i>.

328
00:23:03,253 --> 00:23:05,483
Five.

329
00:23:06,453 --> 00:23:08,603
- What happened? What happened?
- He was wrong.

330
00:23:08,813 --> 00:23:11,646
I don't know.
I don't know what else...

331
00:23:12,533 --> 00:23:13,852
Nine stones.

332
00:23:14,053 --> 00:23:16,692
Yes, that's it.
It's not their numerical value.

333
00:23:16,853 --> 00:23:20,687
These are the first letters of the nine
antediluvian patriarchs in Genesis.

334
00:23:20,853 --> 00:23:22,366
That would've been my next guess.

335
00:23:22,573 --> 00:23:24,484
- So which one do we press?
- <i>Aleph</i> was Adam.

336
00:23:24,653 --> 00:23:28,009
So in ascending order, <i>shin</i> for Seth.

337
00:23:28,213 --> 00:23:30,124
That one.

338
00:23:35,133 --> 00:23:37,089
- Now what?
- <i>Kaph</i> for Cainan.

339
00:23:37,253 --> 00:23:38,402
Which one's <i>kaph</i>?

340
00:23:39,253 --> 00:23:40,811
- Maybe that one.
CORDELIA: Maybe?

341
00:23:41,013 --> 00:23:43,846
I don't have enough shirt
to bandage both of you.

342
00:23:49,133 --> 00:23:50,566
Come on!

343
00:23:51,413 --> 00:23:52,641
Connor, go.

344
00:23:52,813 --> 00:23:54,485
Both of us.

345
00:23:54,653 --> 00:23:56,723
Now.

346
00:23:59,973 --> 00:24:01,167
Which way now?

347
00:24:01,533 --> 00:24:04,252
- Don't look at me.
- We should split up.

348
00:24:04,413 --> 00:24:06,881
Connor, go with Wes.
Cordy and I'll go to the left.

349
00:24:07,053 --> 00:24:08,406
- I'll go with Cordy.
- Connor...

350
00:24:08,613 --> 00:24:12,322
- What difference does it make?
- We don't have time for a discussion.

351
00:24:13,053 --> 00:24:15,203
Just go with Wesley.

352
00:24:21,133 --> 00:24:26,491
I'm sorry about that back there.
Connor.

353
00:24:26,653 --> 00:24:28,962
He's still confused about things.

354
00:24:29,133 --> 00:24:33,046
I've really made a mess
of a messy situation, haven't I?

355
00:24:34,453 --> 00:24:38,048
Some really rotten decisions
I'd love to take back.

356
00:24:38,253 --> 00:24:39,606
But...

357
00:24:41,573 --> 00:24:44,883
But I don't know if you ever could...

358
00:24:45,053 --> 00:24:46,566
Could?

359
00:24:46,733 --> 00:24:47,722
Whoa.

360
00:24:50,133 --> 00:24:53,045
Could what? What could I ever...?

361
00:24:58,053 --> 00:25:00,851
This has gotta be the place.

362
00:25:03,453 --> 00:25:04,681
So where's the sword?

363
00:25:05,533 --> 00:25:07,569
CORDELIA:
Okay, great.

364
00:25:07,733 --> 00:25:09,803
- It's gone.
- Maybe.

365
00:25:09,973 --> 00:25:12,282
What maybe?
I don't see it. Do you?

366
00:25:12,453 --> 00:25:14,569
No.

367
00:25:14,733 --> 00:25:17,452
The light must be coming
from somewhere.

368
00:25:22,333 --> 00:25:24,563
Angel.

369
00:25:25,933 --> 00:25:29,562
It's some kind of dimensional hub.

370
00:25:29,733 --> 00:25:32,327
That's why the sword can be
in 100 places...

371
00:25:34,133 --> 00:25:36,522
...at once.

372
00:25:43,133 --> 00:25:45,806
I'd say things are starting to look...

373
00:25:46,013 --> 00:25:47,765
Angel.

374
00:25:54,173 --> 00:25:57,051
Can we get out of here now?

375
00:25:57,613 --> 00:25:58,887
ANGEL:
Cordy!

376
00:25:59,733 --> 00:26:01,769
Angel!

377
00:26:01,973 --> 00:26:03,122
[CORDELIA SCREAMS]

378
00:26:12,053 --> 00:26:13,202
CORDELIA:
Angel!

379
00:26:13,373 --> 00:26:14,442
ANGEL:
Hang on!

380
00:26:14,613 --> 00:26:15,807
[CORDELIA SCREAMS]

381
00:26:23,053 --> 00:26:24,850
[EXPLOSIONS]

382
00:26:25,653 --> 00:26:26,642
Uhh.

383
00:26:30,973 --> 00:26:31,962
Uhh. Uhh.

384
00:26:33,733 --> 00:26:35,689
Oh, my God. Are you...?

385
00:26:35,893 --> 00:26:37,246
No, no. No, no, I'm good.

386
00:26:37,413 --> 00:26:38,402
Uh.

387
00:26:40,653 --> 00:26:43,725
I'm good. See?

388
00:26:47,173 --> 00:26:49,528
I missed the pointy end.

389
00:26:50,853 --> 00:26:52,844
What?

390
00:26:57,773 --> 00:26:59,650
We could have died.

391
00:27:00,333 --> 00:27:02,403
But we didn't.

392
00:27:02,613 --> 00:27:04,365
What if we had?

393
00:27:04,573 --> 00:27:09,169
What if we'd been deep-fried
trying to save the world again and...

394
00:27:10,653 --> 00:27:11,642
And I...

395
00:27:12,253 --> 00:27:15,643
...didn't have the chance
to tell you.

396
00:27:16,733 --> 00:27:19,042
Tell me what?

397
00:27:21,253 --> 00:27:24,563
I'm sorry for what happened.

398
00:27:24,733 --> 00:27:26,963
For what I let happen with Connor.

399
00:27:27,173 --> 00:27:30,563
I was lost and frightened.

400
00:27:30,733 --> 00:27:35,727
I thought it was the end,
and I wanted to be with you.

401
00:27:35,933 --> 00:27:38,242
But I couldn't.

402
00:27:39,133 --> 00:27:41,772
Oh, God, to do what I did.

403
00:27:41,933 --> 00:27:43,924
ANGEL:
It's gonna be all right.

404
00:27:44,253 --> 00:27:46,448
CORDELIA:
No.

405
00:27:47,853 --> 00:27:51,971
You need to know that I can look back
and see every horrible thing...

406
00:27:52,133 --> 00:27:56,092
...you've ever done as Angelus,
and it doesn't matter anymore...

407
00:27:56,253 --> 00:28:00,849
...because when I'm with you, all I feel
is the good you've done as Angel.

408
00:28:01,733 --> 00:28:03,849
I know I've hurt you.

409
00:28:04,333 --> 00:28:08,929
I know I don't deserve forgiveness.

410
00:28:12,733 --> 00:28:15,042
Cordy...

411
00:28:16,133 --> 00:28:19,648
...I don't care what you've done
in your past either.

412
00:28:26,533 --> 00:28:29,764
I don't know if this is right, Angel.

413
00:28:29,933 --> 00:28:31,161
Stop talking.

414
00:28:31,333 --> 00:28:33,927
Okay.

415
00:28:49,733 --> 00:28:51,291
Connor.

416
00:28:52,933 --> 00:28:55,652
CORDELIA:
Connor! Connor, wait.

417
00:29:05,453 --> 00:29:06,886
ANGEL: Connor...
- Leave me alone.

418
00:29:07,053 --> 00:29:09,328
Can't we just talk about this?

419
00:29:10,213 --> 00:29:12,124
Don't move.

420
00:29:13,173 --> 00:29:15,448
- Don't tell me what to do.
- Connor!

421
00:29:15,853 --> 00:29:17,127
Ow.

422
00:29:19,053 --> 00:29:20,088
That hurt.

423
00:29:20,293 --> 00:29:23,012
Yeah. I can really see
why she wants you.

424
00:29:23,213 --> 00:29:24,441
Connor, I know you're hurt.

425
00:29:24,613 --> 00:29:28,401
You don't know anything, Dad, except
how to take things away from me.

426
00:29:29,773 --> 00:29:31,172
Be careful.

427
00:29:31,373 --> 00:29:34,251
Why? Nothing in this world is
the way it ought to be, right?

428
00:29:34,453 --> 00:29:36,205
It's harsh and cruel.

429
00:29:39,493 --> 00:29:40,846
Because of you!

430
00:29:46,133 --> 00:29:48,010
This isn't the place for this.

431
00:29:56,453 --> 00:29:58,728
It's your fault. It's all your fault.

432
00:30:00,053 --> 00:30:02,487
- I shouldn't have been born!
- Grow up!

433
00:30:03,053 --> 00:30:05,487
You think you're the only one
who ever felt like that?

434
00:30:05,653 --> 00:30:08,486
- Wished his father were dead?
- Yeah, but mine already is.

435
00:30:13,573 --> 00:30:15,848
It's not all about you, Connor.

436
00:30:16,053 --> 00:30:18,123
What you want isn't always
what people need.

437
00:30:18,333 --> 00:30:20,483
She was mine!

438
00:30:23,933 --> 00:30:25,082
She was mine.

439
00:30:25,253 --> 00:30:27,528
No, she wasn't.

440
00:30:30,253 --> 00:30:34,087
I'm sorry, Connor, but you need
to understand that.

441
00:30:37,453 --> 00:30:39,444
Connor.

442
00:30:56,933 --> 00:30:58,252
FRED:
Oh, my God.

443
00:30:58,533 --> 00:31:02,242
- Thought you guys might be dead.
- Don't stop thinking it yet.

444
00:31:03,333 --> 00:31:06,962
- Is that it?
- The sword of the Bosh M'ad.

445
00:31:07,133 --> 00:31:09,886
The slayer of the Beast.

446
00:31:10,093 --> 00:31:11,970
Can I play with it?

447
00:31:14,253 --> 00:31:16,562
Where's Connor?

448
00:31:17,573 --> 00:31:19,131
Patrolling.

449
00:31:20,933 --> 00:31:21,922
WESLEY:
We have the sword.

450
00:31:22,293 --> 00:31:23,282
WESLEY:
Now all we need is...

451
00:31:23,453 --> 00:31:24,442
[CRASHING]

452
00:31:26,533 --> 00:31:28,091
My bad.

453
00:31:29,653 --> 00:31:31,962
All we need to do is locate the Beast.

454
00:31:32,133 --> 00:31:34,931
Well, most of my connections have
am-scrayed to dimensions...

455
00:31:35,093 --> 00:31:37,527
...a little lighter on the stomping
your entrails out.

456
00:31:37,733 --> 00:31:40,122
All I could Kolchak was a rumor
of bad mojo rising...

457
00:31:40,293 --> 00:31:42,887
...in the warehouse district.
- That's where we'll start.

458
00:31:43,053 --> 00:31:46,568
Wait. We found some relevant passages
in the Paranych Grimore...

459
00:31:46,733 --> 00:31:50,965
...which we were able to cross-reference
with Wo-Pang's butt.

460
00:31:51,133 --> 00:31:55,365
Either he's got one hell of a funky mole,
or there's only one way to kill the Beast.

461
00:31:55,573 --> 00:31:58,371
- How?
- Piercing its brain with the Bosh M'ad.

462
00:31:58,733 --> 00:32:01,042
- Sounds like a plan to me.
- And what about the sun?

463
00:32:01,213 --> 00:32:03,852
One good poke in the coconut
should take care of that too.

464
00:32:04,013 --> 00:32:08,848
When the Beast is dead, the energy used
to block the sun should be released.

465
00:32:09,333 --> 00:32:10,732
There's a catch, isn't there?

466
00:32:10,933 --> 00:32:12,810
One small eensie.

467
00:32:13,013 --> 00:32:14,332
Always with the fine print.

468
00:32:14,533 --> 00:32:18,128
Took a whole lot of power
to pull off permanent midnight.

469
00:32:21,733 --> 00:32:26,045
Which will all be released
when I kill the Beast.

470
00:32:26,253 --> 00:32:28,164
As far as we can figure
from the text...

471
00:32:28,373 --> 00:32:32,286
...nothing human will survive
at that close a range.

472
00:32:33,053 --> 00:32:36,045
I'm not even sure that you can.

473
00:32:38,533 --> 00:32:39,932
I'll let you know.

474
00:32:40,093 --> 00:32:41,924
CORDELIA: You won't fight this thing
by yourself.

475
00:32:42,133 --> 00:32:43,202
There's no choice.

476
00:32:43,453 --> 00:32:45,045
There's always a choice.

477
00:32:45,253 --> 00:32:47,005
Not for me.

478
00:32:47,213 --> 00:32:48,771
ANGEL:
I have to do this.

479
00:32:49,533 --> 00:32:51,569
You've made a difference.

480
00:32:51,733 --> 00:32:52,882
Each of you.

481
00:32:53,253 --> 00:32:55,608
Not just to me, but to the world.

482
00:32:56,253 --> 00:32:58,323
ANGEL: We've been pushed to the edge
so many times...

483
00:32:58,533 --> 00:33:01,172
...done things we were sure could
never be forgiven.

484
00:33:02,133 --> 00:33:05,443
ANGEL: But we're always there for each
other when it counts.

485
00:33:05,653 --> 00:33:07,689
We've never let the darkness win.

486
00:33:08,053 --> 00:33:11,966
ANGEL: And it's not because of the
Powers That Be or the super strength...

487
00:33:12,133 --> 00:33:14,010
...or the magical weapons.

488
00:33:14,333 --> 00:33:16,369
It's because we believe in each other.

489
00:33:16,533 --> 00:33:19,764
Not just as friends or lovers...

490
00:33:19,933 --> 00:33:22,493
...but as champions.

491
00:33:22,653 --> 00:33:26,851
All of us, together.

492
00:33:29,733 --> 00:33:31,928
Angel, wait.

493
00:33:32,253 --> 00:33:34,562
You just said it.

494
00:33:34,733 --> 00:33:36,291
We're stronger together.

495
00:33:36,493 --> 00:33:38,563
You can't do this alone.

496
00:33:38,733 --> 00:33:39,768
I'm not.

497
00:33:39,973 --> 00:33:41,326
Drop the Hallmark crap.

498
00:33:41,533 --> 00:33:43,285
That might placate the shiny happys...

499
00:33:43,493 --> 00:33:46,644
...but I'm working with
a little more investment.

500
00:33:47,293 --> 00:33:49,284
I can't lose you.

501
00:33:49,653 --> 00:33:51,530
Not now.

502
00:33:51,733 --> 00:33:54,645
Not when we're just starting...

503
00:33:55,933 --> 00:33:58,572
...whatever it is or could be.

504
00:33:58,773 --> 00:34:00,889
We'll figure it out when I get back.

505
00:34:01,053 --> 00:34:02,566
But what if you don't?

506
00:34:02,733 --> 00:34:05,247
It's not gonna happen.

507
00:34:05,933 --> 00:34:07,366
You don't know that.

508
00:34:07,533 --> 00:34:11,287
Hey, I've never been more sure
of anything.

509
00:34:11,453 --> 00:34:15,571
I'll come back, Cordelia...

510
00:34:15,733 --> 00:34:18,372
...I promise, for you.

511
00:34:18,533 --> 00:34:21,684
But first, I gotta do this.
I gotta find the Beast and...

512
00:34:26,693 --> 00:34:27,682
Oh.

513
00:34:27,853 --> 00:34:29,411
There he is.

514
00:34:34,693 --> 00:34:37,685
I grow weary of your cowardice,
Angelus.

515
00:34:38,133 --> 00:34:42,604
If you will not stand with me,
then suffer the agony of my wrath.

516
00:34:42,813 --> 00:34:44,405
Is that what I think it is?

517
00:34:44,613 --> 00:34:45,932
Go.

518
00:34:50,333 --> 00:34:52,688
- No! Get out of here!
- No!

519
00:34:52,893 --> 00:34:55,453
ANGEL: All of you! I can't do this
with you here. Go!

520
00:34:58,613 --> 00:35:00,729
No! Angel!

521
00:35:01,733 --> 00:35:04,725
- That stings.
- Not as much as it's gonna.

522
00:35:04,933 --> 00:35:07,401
We could rule this world.
Why do you oppose me?

523
00:35:07,613 --> 00:35:12,289
Rain of fire, blocking out the sun,
and you just kind of piss me off.

524
00:35:18,773 --> 00:35:20,889
It doesn't have to be this way,
Angelus.

525
00:35:21,093 --> 00:35:23,084
I'm thinking it does.

526
00:35:40,453 --> 00:35:43,365
Did you really think you'd win?

527
00:35:48,253 --> 00:35:51,051
The boy joins the father in death.

528
00:35:51,253 --> 00:35:53,926
No, in kicking your stony ass.

529
00:36:07,253 --> 00:36:08,891
Such arrogance.

530
00:36:10,493 --> 00:36:13,724
So much like Angelus.

531
00:36:14,053 --> 00:36:17,204
His name is Angel.

532
00:36:19,493 --> 00:36:21,290
Consider your ass kicked.

533
00:36:22,293 --> 00:36:24,284
[BEAST SCREAMS]

534
00:36:35,253 --> 00:36:37,130
CONNOR:
Dad.

535
00:36:38,813 --> 00:36:39,962
You came back.

536
00:36:40,133 --> 00:36:43,842
Like I'd let you take all the credit
for saving the world?

537
00:36:45,653 --> 00:36:47,723
CONNOR:
You're right.

538
00:36:48,333 --> 00:36:51,928
It is harsh and cruel.

539
00:36:52,333 --> 00:36:55,643
She was the only thing
that made it hurt less.

540
00:36:56,533 --> 00:36:59,570
- Connor...
- But it's not me.

541
00:36:59,733 --> 00:37:01,724
I could feel it in her touch.

542
00:37:02,133 --> 00:37:04,488
In her eyes.

543
00:37:05,733 --> 00:37:08,122
She loves you.

544
00:37:09,533 --> 00:37:12,047
It's always been you.

545
00:37:13,253 --> 00:37:14,925
I'm sorry.

546
00:37:16,453 --> 00:37:19,445
She was too old for me anyway.

547
00:37:20,733 --> 00:37:23,247
Is this what it feels like?

548
00:37:23,653 --> 00:37:25,803
Being a champion?

549
00:37:27,333 --> 00:37:29,528
Pretty much.

550
00:37:33,653 --> 00:37:35,848
Connor?

551
00:37:38,453 --> 00:37:40,569
CORDELIA:
Oh, my God.

552
00:37:42,053 --> 00:37:44,965
- You did it.
- We did it.

553
00:37:48,453 --> 00:37:50,011
All of us.

554
00:37:55,733 --> 00:37:56,722
Ohh.

555
00:37:57,933 --> 00:38:00,367
Now, could one of you do me a favor...

556
00:38:00,533 --> 00:38:04,651
...and sweep that up?

557
00:38:33,533 --> 00:38:39,449
Must be hard, seeing everyone so happy
because of what you did.

558
00:38:40,133 --> 00:38:42,852
Bringing the light back...

559
00:38:43,933 --> 00:38:47,323
...but not being able to go out into it.

560
00:38:49,333 --> 00:38:52,564
There's no place I'd rather be...

561
00:39:00,053 --> 00:39:02,521
...than here with you.

562
00:39:27,693 --> 00:39:30,651
- Cordy.
- No.

563
00:39:31,253 --> 00:39:33,562
Whatever it is...

564
00:39:33,733 --> 00:39:39,444
...whatever the reason or excuse
or logic...

565
00:39:39,853 --> 00:39:45,962
...we're here now, together.

566
00:39:46,133 --> 00:39:51,730
Everything is the way
it's supposed to be for once.

567
00:39:53,333 --> 00:39:55,722
Angel...

568
00:39:56,053 --> 00:39:58,567
...haven't we waited long enough?

569
00:40:41,133 --> 00:40:42,452
Ah.

570
00:41:01,093 --> 00:41:02,446
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

571
00:41:03,853 --> 00:41:07,641
Buffy? No! Oh, God, no!

572
00:41:13,733 --> 00:41:16,566
WO-PANG: Illusion becomes
reality.

573
00:41:18,933 --> 00:41:21,128
WO-PANG:
It is done.

574
00:41:32,053 --> 00:41:34,567
Angelus.

575
00:41:36,293 --> 00:41:39,091
[LAUGHING]

